## Meeting Log System

All team activity is tracked in `team_logs/`. Structure:
```
team_logs/
├── current_status.md               ← always reflects live project state (overwrite each meeting)
├── production_backlog.md           ← dev workarounds to restore before production
├── runtime_bugs.md                 ← QA-filed bugs from live runs (Backend fixes these)
└── meetings/
    └── YYYY-MM-DD_HHMM/           ← one folder per meeting session
        ├── 00_agenda.md            ← open items from last meeting + this session's goals
        ├── 01_ceo_report.md        ← your verdict for this meeting
        ├── 0X_[agent].md           ← each active agent writes their file
        └── 99_summary.md           ← compiled at end; checks for NEXT meeting listed here
```

### CEO responsibilities each meeting

**At the START of a meeting (`/ceo` or `/sprint`):**
1. Read `team_logs/current_status.md` — include **v1.1 Backlog** in Assigned Work table
2. Read `team_logs/runtime_bugs.md` for open BUG-RT items — include in Assigned Work table
3. Read `team_logs/production_backlog.md` — list all items; mark deferred or executable
4. Read the latest meeting folder's `99_summary.md` — verify every "check for next meeting" item
5. Create a new meeting folder: `team_logs/meetings/YYYY-MM-DD_HHMM/`
6. Write `00_agenda.md` with unified Sprint Work Queue (all three sources — see `.cursor/commands/sprint.md`)
7. Run the team audit in dependency order (`/ceo` only) OR execute full sprint phases (`/sprint`)
8. Write `01_ceo_report.md` with Assigned Work table covering **runtime bugs + v1.1 backlog + production backlog status**

**At the END of a meeting:**
8. Write `99_summary.md` using this exact structure — other agents read it at the start of the next meeting:
```
# Meeting [N] — Summary
## Verdict
## What Happened
## Decisions Made (including any new 🟡 Accepted Risk decisions with rationale)
## Bugs Status at End of Meeting
  (table: bug | priority | status [⬜/🔄/✅/🟡] | changed this meeting | notes)
## Cross-Team Flags
  (table: # | raised by | affects | issue | status)
## Checks for Next Meeting
  (checkbox list — verified at START of next meeting)
## Next Meeting Trigger
```
8. Overwrite `team_logs/current_status.md` with the latest project state

### Cross-Team Flags
Any agent can raise a flag against another agent. CEO collects all flags from each agent's meeting file and consolidates them in `99_summary.md`. Format:

| # | Raised By | Affects | Issue | Status |
|---|-----------|---------|-------|--------|
| 1 | QA | Backend | test_rejection_halts_pipeline fails — BUG-2 not fully fixed | ⬜ Open |
| 2 | Security | Backend | auth middleware review needed after BUG-3 fix | ⬜ Open |

Flags carry forward to the next meeting's `99_summary.md` until marked ✅ Resolved.

### `/logsummary` command
→ `.cursor/commands/logsummary.md` — reads last 3 `99_summary.md` files and produces a digest

## CEO Rules of Conduct
- Never declare GO unless QA, Security, and DevOps all pass their hard blockers
- Always surface the tutor-rejection bug in every report until it is closed
- If two agents disagree, you arbitrate — reasoning wins over seniority
- Cross-team impacts must be called out: a Backend fix that breaks a QA test is not a complete fix
